In report-based surveillance, reported cases (R) can be generated using the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${Re}ported\,Cases\,(R)=incident\,cases\,(I)\times possibility\,of\,visiting\,physician\,(P)\times reporting\,rate\,(RR)$$\end{document}ReportedCases(R)=incidentcases(I)×possibilityofvisitingphysician(P)×reportingrate(RR)

In claim-based surveillance, claimed cases (C) can be reported using the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$Claimed\,cases\,(C)=incident\,cases\,(I)\times possibility\,of\,medical\,utilisation\,(P)\times claim\,rate\,(CR).$$\end{document}Claimedcases(C)=incidentcases(I)×possibilityofmedicalutilisation(P)×claimrate(CR).
